This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama in May 2012. The memorandum discusses the designation of officers within the Office of Personnel Management (OPM) to act as the Director of OPM in the event that the current Director and Deputy Director are unable to perform their duties. The memorandum provides a specific order of succession for these officers to assume the role of Director. It also includes exceptions, stating that individuals serving in an acting capacity or not eligible under the law cannot act as Director. The President retains discretion to depart from this memorandum when designating an acting Director. This memorandum supersedes a previous one issued in 2005. It concludes by stating that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits and directs the publication of the memorandum in the Federal Register.